complete hospital chains

72
00:04:12,013 --> 00:04:15,013
with donor support from
industrialised countries.

73
00:04:15,566 --> 00:04:18,854
An NGO located in 
an industrial country

74
00:04:19,054 --> 00:04:22,729
may decide to purchase a batch
of x-ray systems

75
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:25,929
to be then commissioned in several
hospitals, 

76
00:04:26,129 --> 00:04:29,129
even if that NGO 
has no real presence

77
00:04:29,329 --> 00:04:30,566
in the country.

78
00:04:31,721 --> 00:04:34,946
This customer segment
has specific concerns.

79
00:04:35,726 --> 00:04:39,251
It wants  to maximise the impact of
donor money.

80
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:42,767
It also needs to show clear metrics
of this impact, 

81
00:04:42,942 --> 00:04:44,867
on the health of beneficiaries.

82
00:04:45,538 --> 00:04:48,375
International NGOs
have more flexibility

83
00:04:48,575 --> 00:04:51,575
in resources allocation than
the Ministry of Health,

84
00:04:51,775 --> 00:04:55,238
and their decision processes 
are usually much shorter.

85
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:58,320
Yet another type of customers

86
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:01,820
who might be interested in buying
such an x-ray machine

87
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:05,757
are national and international
development aid agencies.

88
00:05:06,157 --> 00:05:08,695
Like the SDC in Switzerland, 

89
00:05:08,895 --> 00:05:10,870
USAID  in the US, 

90
00:05:11,070 --> 00:05:12,607
the GIZ in Germany,

91
00:05:12,807 --> 00:05:16,895
the JICA in Japan, or like
the African Development Bank.

92
00:05:17,649 --> 00:05:20,774
The basic job-to-be-done
by these institutions

93
00:05:20,974 --> 00:05:24,174
is to foster the development
of less developed countries, 

94
00:05:24,374 --> 00:05:26,574
and to strengthen international
cooperation.

95
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:30,482
They are concerned that the money 
they put into projects,

96
00:05:30,682 --> 00:05:33,295
has a long lasting positive
impact, 

97
00:05:33,495 --> 00:05:36,957
and that it empowers people
in the targeted countries.

98
00:05:38,092 --> 00:05:41,917
Note that we are using different 
colours for each customer segment.

99
00:05:42,490 --> 00:05:45,865
This is important, because we know, 
that each segment

100
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:49,529
will potentially have to be dealt
with in a different way,

101
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:52,708
as we build up the complete canvas.

102
00:05:53,359 --> 00:05:55,447
For the sake of simplicity however, 

103
00:05:55,647 --> 00:05:59,084
we will only present the business
model for the first customer segment

104
00:05:59,284 --> 00:06:01,172
in the rest of this example.

105
00:06:01,769 --> 00:06:05,344
Now that we have seen which customer
segment we want to target,

106
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:08,303
let us see which aspect
of the x-ray machine

107
00:06:08,503 --> 00:06:10,240
can be interesting to them.

108
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:13,843
We have seen that the hospitals
have limited budgets

109
00:06:14,043 --> 00:06:17,505
to buy new equipment and usually
no budget for its maintenance.

110
00:06:18,293 --> 00:06:23,218
We thus have to come up with
an attractive pricing proposition.

111
00:06:23,751 --> 00:06:27,013
In general, x-ray systems
are sold together

112
00:06:27,213 --> 00:06:30,413
with a maintenance contract which
can be very expensive,

113
00:06:30,613 --> 00:06:34,201
and represents typically 10% of
the initial purchase price

114
00:06:34,401 --> 00:06:37,676
to be paid each and every year
to the manufacturer.

115
00:06:38,528 --> 00:06:41,703
Also, there is the cost
of the consumables 

116
00:06:41,903 --> 00:06:43,778
such as films and chemicals.

117
00:06:44,306 --> 00:06:47,881
If the customer wants to reduce
the total cost of ownership,

118
00:06:48,342 --> 00:06:51,805
it means to reduce the sum
of all these costs.

119
00:06:52,715 --> 00:06:54,802
Since our concept is digital,

120
00:06:55,002 --> 00:06:57,752
the costs of films and chemicals
are spared,

121
00:06:57,952 --> 00:07:00,652
which reduces the total cost 
of ownership.

122
00:07:01,203 --> 00:07:04,966
Also, since it has been redesigned
for the local context,

123
00:07:05,166 --> 00:07:08,166
and it is very robust, 
maintenance and repair costs

124
00:07:08,366 --> 00:07:10,003
will also be reduced.

125
00:07:11,114 --> 00:07:14,301
Our value proposition is thus
a reduced

126
00:07:14,619 --> 00:07:16,894
total cost of ownership or TCO.

127
00:07:17,394 --> 00:07:21,494
The second element is an inherent
robustness of the design

128
00:07:21,694 --> 00:07:24,531
including features such as
a power supply

129
00:07:24,731 --> 00:07:27,869
which resists the local 
electrical instability

130
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:31,813
and a battery to allow 
continuous work

131
00:07:32,013 --> 00:07:34,725
in case of a black-out
for up to an hour.

132
00:07:35,656 --> 00:07:38,806
This robustness reduces the frequent
downtimes

133
00:07:39,299 --> 00:07:42,587
experienced with other systems,
not designed for this context.

134
00:07:43,652 --> 00:07:46,989
Now as we claimed that our
technology is more robust,

135
00:07:47,189 --> 00:07:49,939
and also to address the lack
of maintenance budgets,

136
00:07:50,295 --> 00:07:53,320
we introduce an extended warranty.

137
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:57,520
In other words, an additional aspect
of the value proposition

138
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:02,182
is to include the maintenance fees
in the selling price of the device.

139
00:08:02,725 --> 00:08:06,575
The Ministry will pay only once
to acquire the machine

140
00:08:06,775 --> 00:08:10,425
and then maintenance and repairs
will be provided free of charge

141
00:08:10,625 --> 00:08:13,213
by the company for up to 6 years.

142
00:08:13,747 --> 00:08:17,097
The last crucial element
of the value proposition

143
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:20,492
is the fact that 
the system is digital

144
00:08:20,692 --> 00:08:23,767
which enables the possibility
to transfer images

145
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:27,930
through the internet when available
or via the cell phone network.

146
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:32,178
This feature offers the possibility
to transfer images

147
00:08:32,378 --> 00:08:34,753
to a remotely located specialist

148
00:08:34,953 --> 00:08:38,765
for a second opinion in case
of doubts on a diagnosis.

149
00:08:39,322 --> 00:08:41,035
This is called tele-medicine,

150
00:08:41,235 --> 00:08:43,410
or in this case, tele-radiology, 

151
00:08:43,610 --> 00:08:45,972
and it is particularly interesting
for hospitals

152
00:08:46,172 --> 00:08:48,597
located in remote rural areas.

153
00:08:48,963 --> 00:08:49,938
By definition, 

154
00:08:50,138 --> 00:08:53,551
local hospitals are located
directly in our target country

155
00:08:53,751 --> 00:08:56,576
or countries, possibly 
in remote areas.

156
00:08:56,867 --> 00:09:00,729
Unless the government buys 
a batch of machines centrally,

157
00:09:00,929 --> 00:09:03,842
and takes care of dispatching them
in the country,

158
00:09:04,042 --> 00:09:05,342
which is usually no the case, 

159
00:09:05,542 --> 00:09:08,867
we must manage to deliver the x-ray
machine ourselves.

160
00:09:09,528 --> 00:09:12,016
As we have seen in 
the product value chain,

161
00:09:12,216 --> 00:09:15,491
the distribution channel can be
either a direct sale

162
00:09:15,691 --> 00:09:17,491
from the company to the customer, 

163
00:09:17,691 --> 00:09:20,378
or the product can be sold
though an intermediary.

164
00:09:20,805 --> 00:09:24,492
This intermediary, can be 
an independent partner

165
00:09:24,692 --> 00:09:27,692
or a subsidiary of our own company.

166
00:09:28,249 --> 00:09:30,624
In our case, we decided
to create

167
00:09:30,977 --> 00:09:32,777
a local subsidiary,

168
00:09:32,977 --> 00:09:36,315
through which we will sell directly
to the Ministry of Health.

169
00:09:37,181 --> 00:09:40,206
This has the advantage of keeping
a tighter control

170
00:09:40,406 --> 00:09:44,218
over the activities, especially with
regards to maintenance and repairs.

171
00:09:45,419 --> 00:09:48,181
We decide to accept the challenge

172
00:09:48,381 --> 00:09:50,106
of running a local subsidiary

173
00:09:50,306 --> 00:09:53,206
because we already have a strong
local network.

174
00:09:53,562 --> 00:09:56,125
And we have identified
a local expert

175
00:09:56,325 --> 00:10:00,275
who we want to put in charge of our
operations in Cameroon.

176
00:10:00,842 --> 00:10:04,142
He will be responsible for the sales
to the government,

177
00:10:04,342 --> 00:10:07,030
as well as for the commissioning
of the equipment,

178
00:10:07,230 --> 00:10:10,342
the training of the users, and
the maintenance activities.

179
00:10:11,214 --> 00:10:14,551
As we have seen, maintenance 
activities are very important here.

180
00:10:14,751 --> 00:10:18,851
Since we have decided to provide
an extended warranty for the device

181
00:10:19,251 --> 00:10:20,814
in our value proposition.

182
00:10:21,677 --> 00:10:24,927
Our company must thus
remain very close

183
00:10:25,127 --> 00:10:26,615
to its customers.

184
00:10:27,215 --> 00:10:28,828
Such a local subsidiary

185
00:10:29,028 --> 00:10:33,115
represents also an obvious advantage
in terms of customer relationships.

186
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:36,448
A local subsidiary will
be able to establish

187
00:10:36,648 --> 00:10:39,335
closer relationships with
radiologists

188
00:10:39,535 --> 00:10:41,598
and government representatives
in the country.

189
00:10:41,999 --> 00:10:45,162
It's employees can travel more
easily inside the country, 

190
00:10:45,362 --> 00:10:48,362
even to remote areas 
to provide rapid

191
00:10:48,562 --> 00:10:50,324
local customer service.

192
00:10:51,044 --> 00:10:54,131
They are also likely to share 
a common culture

193
00:10:54,331 --> 00:10:56,306
and language with the customers.

194
00:10:56,795 --> 00:10:59,770
A local subsidiary is in
a good position

195
00:10:59,970 --> 00:11:02,433
to relay country specific issues

196
00:11:02,633 --> 00:11:06,433
that the main company will not
be aware of from a distant country.

197
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:10,825
All this helps to keep customers,
and acquire new ones.

198
00:11:11,559 --> 00:11:14,559
But the next step in acquiring
the first customers

199
00:11:14,759 --> 00:11:17,321
is to involve them into 
the creation process

200
00:11:17,521 --> 00:11:18,434
as we have seen.

201
00:11:18,634 --> 00:11:22,271
This co-creation of the device
with local practitioners

202
00:11:22,471 --> 00:11:25,471
with relevant experience
has 2 effects:

203
00:11:25,755 --> 00:11:27,930
On the one hand it ensures

204
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:32,068
that the device is truly fit for
its purpose and context of use, 

205
00:11:32,592 --> 00:11:34,979
on the other hand, it ensures

206
00:11:35,179 --> 00:11:38,492
the adhesion of the local
practitioners to the product,

207
00:11:38,692 --> 00:11:43,192
which counts a lot because they may 
be the future customers themselves,

208
00:11:43,379 --> 00:11:46,342
or at least be in contact
with customers.

209
00:11:47,610 --> 00:11:50,423
Typical business models in 
the medical technology sector

210
00:11:50,623 --> 00:11:52,660
comprise 3 sources of revenues.

211
00:11:53,152 --> 00:11:55,865
One, the sale of the medical 
device itself,

212
00:11:56,282 --> 00:11:57,895
which is a one-off sale.

213
00:11:58,317 --> 00:12:01,705
Two, the regular sale of consumables
such as reagents

214
00:12:01,905 --> 00:12:04,905
or probes, which is called
recurring sales.

215
00:12:05,105 --> 00:12:09,267
And finally the sale of services
such as installing software upgrades,

216
00:12:09,467 --> 00:12:12,005
performing regular maintenance,
or calibration.

217
00:12:12,431 --> 00:12:16,168
Such a recurring sales model can
be very profitable for the company,

218
00:12:16,368 --> 00:12:19,756
but it leads to a high total cost
of ownership for the customer.

219
00:12:19,956 --> 00:12:23,593
And it does not fit well with how
health care budgets are planned

220
00:12:23,793 --> 00:12:26,793
by governments in many
low-income countries.

221
00:12:28,150 --> 00:12:31,362
Our revenue stream will thus
be made solely

222
00:12:31,562 --> 00:12:33,437
from the sale of the device

223
00:12:33,637 --> 00:12:35,887
which will include 6 years 
of warrranty

224
00:12:36,087 --> 00:12:37,500
as we had said before.

225
00:12:37,912 --> 00:12:40,575
As far as environmental benefits,

226
00:12:40,775 --> 00:12:42,187
there are 2 of them.

227
00:12:42,406 --> 00:12:45,556
First, as already mentioned, the
fact that we use digital

228
00:12:45,756 --> 00:12:47,893
rather than analog radiology,

229
00:12:48,093 --> 00:12:49,931
eliminates the need for chemicals

230
00:12:50,131 --> 00:12:53,131
which would end-up being thrown
into the environment.

231
00:12:54,199 --> 00:12:56,711
One performance indicator 
in this regard

232
00:12:57,024 --> 00:12:59,636
would be the amount 
of chemicals saved

233
00:12:59,836 --> 00:13:02,586
with each radiology done
by the machine.

234
00:13:02,786 --> 00:13:05,786
Another point is the innovative and
long-lasting power source

235
00:13:05,986 --> 00:13:07,549
built in the machine,

236
00:13:07,749 --> 00:13:10,699
which does not rely on
lead acid batteries.

237
00:13:10,899 --> 00:13:14,511
Such batteries are very polluting
and must be replaced frequently.

238
00:13:15,156 --> 00:13:18,056
Here, the number of lead acid
batteries avoided

239
00:13:18,256 --> 00:13:20,093
can be used as a metric.

240
00:13:20,529 --> 00:13:24,391
Finally, the social benefits brought
by each machine

241
00:13:24,717 --> 00:13:28,392
is actually the very impact that
was originally targeted.

242
00:13:28,712 --> 00:13:30,700
As discussed earlier in this MOOC,

243
00:13:30,928 --> 00:13:34,915
it is difficult to disentangle 
the impact coming solely

244
00:13:35,340 --> 00:13:38,803
from our initiative, from other
simultaneous initiatives.

245
00:13:40,115 --> 00:13:43,302
For example, improvement in
road safety laws,

246
00:13:43,659 --> 00:13:47,596
could also contribute to a reduced
morbidity and mortality

247
00:13:47,969 --> 00:13:49,794
due to road traffic accidents.

248
